New operating model

Use three layers from now on:

Layer A — stable backbone

Rarely changed. Only update deliberately at milestone review.

docs/project_vision.md
docs/architecture_invariants.md
docs/target_capabilities.md

Layer B — operational bootstrap

Updated whenever the active state changes.

docs/start_here.md
docs/current_scope.md
docs/next_patch.md

Layer C — historical memory

Keep for traceability, but do not use as primary startup control.

docs/status.md
docs/roadmap.md
docs/decision_log.md
docs/session_handover.md
docs/development_policy.md

________________________________________________________________

How to use this going forward

At the end of normal patch work, update only:

docs/start_here.md if the startup truth changed
docs/current_scope.md if current capability changed
docs/next_patch.md for the next immediate patch

Only at milestone review or strategic reset, update:

docs/project_vision.md
docs/architecture_invariants.md
docs/target_capabilities.md

That prevents relay drift.